          <h3>Flo</h3>
          <p style="background: lightgray; padding: 10px;">HapiFlo, is an audio-guided yoga app for iPhone. You can think of it like the HeadSpace of yoga. The preference of auditory over visual cues enables users to maintain proper alignment, eliminating the need to strain to look at a screen. We have designed our cues to instruct body motions such as “inhale and lift the arms overhead, while making sure to keep the shoulders away from the ears”, instead of difficult to pronounce and unaccessible ancient names for postures. We also include cues for breath that are taken from extensive study of yoga. Finally, the app tracks changes in relevant biometrics over time, to quantitatively reflect your progress. We want to make a product that will enable a stressed out yoga beginner to practice yoga and relieve his/her stress blindfolded. This means that our cues are so comprehensive, thanks to rigorous testing, that they will help you align your body, mind, and breath. Enter our alpha testing in the top left corner of the screen!</p> 
