          <h3>About</h3>
          <p style="background: lightgray; padding: 10px;">The history of Tamara and Grant's involvement in HapiFlo, started in January 2017 where Tamara started working on the idea for HapiFlo without realizing that it would later become the first product of Hapi Inc. In January and February, Tamara did research about the problem space and learned about the pitfalls of existing methods of managing stress. She used user-centered design to address the needs of college students she knew who were stressed, broke and regularly suffering from the negative consequences of their self-sabotaging health choices. She created the first interactive alpha webapp version March. Then, she focused on school while she accumulated user testing data.
            When Tamara met Grant in March they were working on their other project about food consumption, described above. Grant liked the idea of starting a yoga app, and they began working on the business side of it together, looking for opportunities and putting themselves out there.
            Since July, we have been working part time on HapiFlo, while also doing Yoga Teacher Training and taking classes in Machine Learning so that we will be able to write our own data analysis algorithms. We are also in the myStartupXX accelerator at the Rady School of Management at UCSD.
            As of the fall, Grant is focused full time on the development of HapiFlo and Tamara is part time. When she graduates this year, she will also be full time invested in this project. </p>
